# Code Review Checklist

Use this checklist when reviewing PRs. Not every dimension applies to every change -- focus on what's relevant.

## 1. Correctness

- [ ] Does the code do what it claims?
- [ ] Are edge cases handled (null, empty, boundary values)?
- [ ] Are error paths tested?
- [ ] Does async code handle rejections/exceptions?
- [ ] Are race conditions considered for concurrent operations?

## 2. Security

- [ ] No sensitive data in logs (passwords, tokens, PII, API keys)
- [ ] Input validated on all endpoints / entry points
- [ ] Authentication required where expected
- [ ] Authorization checked at resource level (not just endpoint level)
- [ ] No SQL/NoSQL injection vectors (parameterized queries)
- [ ] No SSRF vectors (URL inputs validated)
- [ ] Rate limiting configured for public endpoints
- [ ] Dependencies scanned for CVEs

## 3. Performance

- [ ] No N+1 query patterns
- [ ] Pagination implemented for list endpoints
- [ ] Appropriate use of caching (and invalidation strategy)
- [ ] Database indexes considered for new queries
- [ ] No blocking operations on async event loops

## 4. Observability

- [ ] Structured logging with context (request ID, user, operation)
- [ ] Health check endpoint updated if new dependencies added
- [ ] Errors logged with enough context to diagnose

## 5. Testing

- [ ] Unit tests for new logic
- [ ] Integration tests for new API endpoints or service interactions
- [ ] Test names are descriptive (`test_<function>_<scenario>`)
- [ ] Mocks are realistic (don't mock away the logic under test)
- [ ] Tests fail when implementation is broken (no test theater)

## 6. Database & Migrations

- [ ] Migration files include both up and down operations
- [ ] Non-reversible migrations clearly documented with rollforward strategy
- [ ] Lock impact assessed for large tables
- [ ] Expand-contract pattern used for non-additive schema changes

## 7. Contract Conformance (API projects)

- [ ] API spec updated before implementation (contract-first)
- [ ] No breaking changes without version bump
- [ ] DTOs / schemas match the spec (types, constraints, required fields)
- [ ] Error responses follow a consistent format

## Review Severity Levels

| Level | Action | Examples |
|-------|--------|---------|
| **Blocker** | Must fix before merge | Security vulnerability, data leak, broken auth, silenced errors |
| **Major** | Should fix before merge | Missing tests, N+1 queries, unvalidated input |
| **Minor** | Fix in follow-up | Naming improvements, additional edge case tests |
| **Nit** | Author's discretion | Style preferences, alternative approaches |
